               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390916-name-1384" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-1384" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-1384" type="surname" value="WOSTER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-1384" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY WOSTER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am foreman to Andrew Spottiswoode and others, of the Gas Light Company. I have missed a great deal of property lately, suspicion was excited by the prisoner appearing very bulky, and told the gate-keeper to stop him—he was searched in my presence, and these two pieces of iron found on him, which I believe to be my master's property—this bolt is a part of an old building.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390916-name-1385" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-1385" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-1385" type="surname" value="FLETCHER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-1385" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>EDWARD FLETCHER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a gate-keeper. I searched the prisoner, and found these pieces of iron—he took the bolt out of his trowsers at the station-house—the iron is laid on one side, what is useful is used again, and the rest is sold.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I was removing some rubbish—I threw this out and thought it was of no value.</p>
